    "body" : "<pre><code>if ((variable == Math.floor(variable)) &amp;&amp; !Double.isInfinite(variable)) {\n    // integer type\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This checks if the rounded-down value of the double is the same as the double.</p>\n\n<p>Your variable could have an int or double value and <code>Math.floor(variable)</code> always has an int value, so if your variable is equal to <code>Math.floor(variable)</code> then it must have an int value.</p>\n\n<p>This also doesn't work if the value of the variable is infinite or negative infinite hence adding 'as long as the variable isn't inifinite' to the condition.</p>\n"
  }, {
