    "question_id" : 9898512,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Consider:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Double.isFinite (value) &amp;&amp; Double.compare (value, StrictMath.rint (value)) == 0\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This sticks to core Java and avoids an equality comparison between floating point values (<code>==</code>) which is consdered bad.  The <code>isFinite()</code> is necessary as <code>rint()</code> will pass-through infinity values.</p>\n"
